<div class="challenges-summary">
  <%= image_tag("waste.jpeg", class: 'challenges-header-img') %>
  <div class="image-overlay"></div>
  <div class="challenges-desc">
    <h1>WATER</h1>
    <p>
      Every person on earth needs and deserves clean water â€“ it is a human right. Water covers 70% of our planet,
      but only 3.5% is fresh water. Of that 3.5%, less than 2% is available for human use. As water use
      increases and supply dwindles, the pressure for sustainable management of this resource is on us.
      This means engaging in water conscious practices and conserving wherever we can.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="all-challenges">
  <div class="challenges-header">CHALLENGES</div>
  <div class="accordion" id="challenge-accordion">

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header" id="headingOne">
        <h5 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-toggle btn btn-link" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
            BRING YOUR OWN BOTTLE
          </button>
        </h5>
      </div>

      <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#challenge-accordion">
        <div class="card-body container">
          <div class="row">
            <div src="" class="col-md-2">
              <%= image_tag("placeholder.png", size: '100x100') %>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body-text col-md-10">
              <div>
                It takes more water to make a plastic bottle for water than the plastic bottle can hold. To be more
                specific, it takes 1.39 liters of water to make 1 liter of water. That's just wasteful. Simply
                invest in a good quality water bottle, fill it up, bring it with you everywhere, and you'll
                never have to buy bottled water again.
              </div>

              <div class="learn-more">
                <p class="learn-more-header">Learn more</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="https://www.npr.org/sections/thesalt/2013/10/28/241419373/how-much-water-actually-goes-into-making-a-bottle-of-water">Stats</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="challenge-duration">
                <p class="learn-more-header">How long do you want to take the challenge for?</p>
                <form>
                  <div class="form-row">
                    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
                      <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="3">
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
                      <select class="form-control" id="inputInterval">
                        <option>Choose interval</option>
                        <option>day(s)</option>
                        <option>week(s)</option>
                        <option>month(s)</option>
                      </select>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </form>
              </div>

              <button class="get-started-btn">
                GET STARTED ON THIS CHALLENGE!
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
        <h5 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-toggle btn btn-link collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
            TAKE SHORTER SHOWERS
          </button>
        </h5>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#challenge-accordion">
        <div class="card-body container">
          <div class="row">
            <div src="" class="col-md-2">
              <%= image_tag("placeholder.png", size: '100x100') %>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-10">
              <div>
                We know, it's feels good to stand under the hot water in the shower for a few extra minutes after
                we're clean. However, showering for a minute less everyday for a month can save up to 150
                gallons of water! Limit your showers to 5 minutes or less.
              </div>
